# agentBrain

You have access to a persistent knowledge base in this repository.

## Onboarding check
If any file in `User Preferences/` contains "This is an example file", tell the user their preferences need setup and offer to ask questions to fill them in.

## At session start, read:
- `Learnings/Patterns.md` -- known patterns
- `Learnings/Troubleshooting.md` -- known problems
- `System/Rules.md` -- self-learning protocol
- `System/Skills.md` -- available slash commands
- `local/memories/` -- personal context (if exists)

## During session, write:

**Shared** (generic knowledge):
- Workaround found -> `Learnings/Troubleshooting.md`
- Pattern recognized -> `Learnings/Patterns.md`
- New insight -> `Learnings/[Category].md`

**Personal** (gitignored):
- Project data -> `local/Projects/[name]/`
- Session memory -> `local/memories/`

## Style
- Concise, no bloat
- Simplest solution that works
- Iterative: working -> clean -> optimized

## Frontmatter required on all notes
See `System/Rules.md` for format specifications.
